# TD-MPC2 walk experiment queue — one JSON spec per line; '#'/blank lines ignored.
# The supervisor runs these in order, each warm-started from the best genuine walker so far
# ("warm_start":"best"; falls back to _preserved/stand_v4_best.pt until the first win).
# Spec fields:
#   name         short id (used in log filenames + journal)
#   warm_start   "best" | "stand_v4" | "scratch" | "<path-to.pt>"
#   variant      train.py --variant (default "walk-biped-tdmpc")
#   flags        extra train.py CLI args (list of strings), e.g. the command curriculum
#   overrides    dotted-path env_cfg patches (ONLY existing reward/termination terms — adding a
#                brand-new reward term needs a Python edit to HybridRewardsCfg, not an override)
#   max_env_steps  per-run budget (default 10_000_000); early-stop rules cut bad runs sooner
#   notes        why — copied into the journal
# Interleaves the two families: command-curriculum runs and reward-weight tweaks. The Claude
# advisor appends new specs below reacting to observed failure modes (see advisor_prompt.md).
# v5 reorder (2026-07-22): the live run confirmed the "upright but won't step / standing is a free
# optimum" failure, so reward-C-pushmove (attack that root cause) runs FIRST, curriculum second.
{"name": "reward-C-pushmove", "warm_start": "stand_v4", "variant": "walk-biped-tdmpc", "overrides": {"rewards.stand_walk.params.move_weight": 0.9}, "notes": "V5 run 1: shift the gated core reward toward MOVING (0.75->0.9) so standing still earns less -> forces stepping. Direct fix for the confirmed 'won't step' plateau. Warm-start the clean stand."}
{"name": "curriculum-A", "warm_start": "best", "variant": "walk-biped-tdmpc", "flags": ["--cmd_curriculum", "--cmd_survive_frac", "0.35"], "notes": "SPINE: survival-gated command ramp 0->full. Ramp speed only once it survives."}
{"name": "reward-A-stride", "warm_start": "best", "variant": "walk-biped-tdmpc", "overrides": {"rewards.feet_air_time.params.air_hi": 0.45, "rewards.feet_air_time.params.air_lo": 0.22}, "notes": "Widen the foot-strike air-time band toward a longer stride (was 0.20-0.40)."}
{"name": "curriculum-B-slow", "warm_start": "best", "variant": "walk-biped-tdmpc", "flags": ["--cmd_curriculum", "--cmd_survive_frac", "0.45", "--cmd_ramp_interval", "80000"], "notes": "Slower, stricter curriculum: prove survival harder (0.45) and ramp less often before speeding up."}
# 2026-07-22 REORDER (idx4+): the _find_run_dir race robbed EVERY curriculum run (idx1,3 got the
# prior reward run's exact grade). Race now fixed (log-parse + pre-launch snapshot). Curriculum was
# the ONLY direction to produce real forward motion (0.39 m/s), so it runs NEXT. The robbed retry
# warm-starts stand_v4 (the clean base that produced 0.39), NOT "best" (=a 0.19 non-walker).
{"name": "curriculum-A2-retry", "warm_start": "stand_v4", "variant": "walk-biped-tdmpc", "flags": ["--cmd_curriculum", "--cmd_survive_frac", "0.35"], "notes": "FAITHFUL retry of curriculum-A (robbed by the race at 26k despite reaching speed->0.39). Clean-stand base + survival-gated ramp. This is the most promising direction; race is fixed so it now gets a real 2M+ evaluation."}
{"name": "curriculum-C-frombest", "warm_start": "best", "variant": "walk-biped-tdmpc", "flags": ["--cmd_curriculum", "--cmd_survive_frac", "0.40"], "notes": "Second curriculum shot from the best-so-far (a moving base if the retry walked, else the 0.19 stand) to push speed higher."}
{"name": "reward-B-noslip", "warm_start": "best", "variant": "walk-biped-tdmpc", "overrides": {"rewards.feet_slide.weight": -0.12, "rewards.upright_bonus.weight": 0.4}, "notes": "Punish foot drag harder + hold posture more upright (the run 3-4 'leaning fakes velocity' fix)."}
{"name": "reward-D-smooth", "warm_start": "best", "variant": "walk-biped-tdmpc", "overrides": {"rewards.action_rate_l2.weight": -0.03}, "notes": "If it walks but jitters: mild extra jerk penalty on the existing action_rate term (keep small so it doesn't barber the gait)."}
# 2026-07-23 advisor: queue was about to run DRY after idx7. Curriculum is OUT (idx4 CURRICULUM_GATE: ramp->1.0 w/ speed 0.107; idx5 warm-base curriculum REWARD-HACKED to fit 0.003). Reward lever WORKS: idx6 reward-B-noslip (feet_slide -0.12 + upright 0.4) = new best 0.325. These two BUILD on that shape (overrides don't persist across runs, so the winning terms are re-specified) + add one push each: force stepping now that posture/no-slip is clean.
{"name": "reward-E-moveslip", "warm_start": "best", "variant": "walk-biped-tdmpc", "overrides": {"rewards.feet_slide.weight": -0.12, "rewards.upright_bonus.weight": 0.4, "rewards.stand_walk.params.move_weight": 0.9}, "notes": "Keep idx6's winning no-slip+upright shape and ADD the move push (move_weight 0.75->0.9). move_weight=0.9 ALONE failed at idx0 because the bot faked motion by sliding/rocking; now that feet_slide is punished, the move push should convert clean posture into real stepping."}
{"name": "reward-F-stride", "warm_start": "best", "variant": "walk-biped-tdmpc", "overrides": {"rewards.feet_slide.weight": -0.12, "rewards.upright_bonus.weight": 0.4, "rewards.feet_air_time.params.air_hi": 0.45, "rewards.feet_air_time.params.air_lo": 0.22}, "notes": "Keep idx6's winning shape + widen the foot-strike air-time band to a longer stride [0.22,0.45]. air_hi=0.45 alone (idx2) only reached 0.19 from the sloppy base; from the cleaner slip-punished base it has a real swing to reward."}
# 2026-07-23 advisor wake4: idx8 reward-E-moveslip (my move_weight 0.9 + no-slip) FAILED to 0.0/fwd -0.0007 -> move_weight bump is POISON (also killed idx0). idx7 reward-D-smooth collapsed to 0.036. idx6 (feet_slide -0.12 + upright 0.4) is a NARROW basin (0.325); aggressive pushes break it. Strategy: single-lever SMALL steps around idx6, NO move_weight. G = reward stepping cadence directly (air_time weight up); I = push the upright lever that already helped one more notch.
{"name": "reward-G-airweight", "warm_start": "best", "variant": "walk-biped-tdmpc", "overrides": {"rewards.feet_slide.weight": -0.12, "rewards.upright_bonus.weight": 0.4, "rewards.feet_air_time.weight": 2.5}, "notes": "Keep idx6 winning shape; raise feet_air_time weight 1.5->2.5 to reward foot-lift/strike CADENCE directly. This is the one locomotion-inducing lever that is NOT move_weight (which is confirmed poison). No-slip base means it can't cheat by dragging."}
{"name": "reward-I-upright5", "warm_start": "best", "variant": "walk-biped-tdmpc", "overrides": {"rewards.feet_slide.weight": -0.12, "rewards.upright_bonus.weight": 0.5}, "notes": "idx6 improved when upright went 0.3->0.4; take ONE more small step to 0.5 (keep feet_slide -0.12). Disciplined single-lever move in the direction that demonstrably worked, avoiding the move_weight poison."}
# 2026-07-23 advisor wake5: BREAKTHROUGH SIGNAL — idx10 reward-G-airweight (feet_air_time.weight 1.5->2.5) hit gs mean 0.149 live @1.85M, the highest SUSTAINED speed of any run (vs idx6 honest 0.042). Cadence reward (NOT move_weight) is the lever that pulls real forward speed. idx9 stride-widen regressed to 0.167; idx8 moveslip 0.0 -> move_weight stays retired. Follow the airweight signal with ONE more small step (weight 3.0). NOTE the feet_air_time here is the uprightness-gated foot-strike-only version (run 0f79... commit), so higher weight is less game-able than the old run-6 leg-wave hack, but watch for reward-hacking at grade if fwd doesn't track.
{"name": "reward-J-airweight3", "warm_start": "best", "variant": "walk-biped-tdmpc", "overrides": {"rewards.feet_slide.weight": -0.12, "rewards.upright_bonus.weight": 0.4, "rewards.feet_air_time.weight": 3.0}, "notes": "idx10 (air_time weight 2.5) gave the best sustained speed yet (gs 0.149). Take ONE more small step to 3.0, keeping idx6's no-slip+upright shape. If idx10/idx11 grades land first and idx10 confirms the win, next wake builds on whichever weight graded best. Watch fwd_speed vs return for hacking."}
